{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"83146c6c-4548-4e01-a372-7902cec8ffa3","content":"Exit code **8** means \"no tests discovered\" — it's a deliberate Microsoft.Testing.Platform behavior that differs from VSTest. Since `INCLUDE_SLOW_TESTS` isn't defined, all test classes are compiled out, triggering this.\n\nThe fix is a single property in your `.csproj`:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_bwzPKhwImK91QpwRbF81UZ","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Fixing zero-tests exit code"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_1uaxMOzY9GiilLmwey2K5w","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-ceed689e34d64090acd492aec2e6d4f0/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n    <!-- Treat zero discovered tests as success (exit code 0 instead of 8) -->\n    <TestingPlatformExitProcessOnMissingTests>false</TestingPlatformExitProcessOnMissingTests>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-ceed689e34d64090acd492aec2e6d4f0/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"1f67e7e9-4651-41b4-b3c4-76a8ec074243","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. With Microsoft.Testing.Platform (enabled via `EnableMSTestRunner`), exit code 8 means \"no tests were found.\" When `INCLUDE_SLOW_TESTS` is not defined, all tests are compiled out, resulting in zero tests, which triggers exit code 8.\n\nThe fix is to set the MSBuild property `<TestingPlatformExitProcessOnMissingTests>false</TestingPlatformExitProcessOnMissingTests>` in the project file. This tells the testing platform to return exit code 0 when no tests are discovered instead of exit code 8.","outputTokens":528},"id":"dd791dde-d532-4e3a-8c88-fab3cefa5acd","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:49:30.293Z","parentId":"35166a78-0f3d-4563-8a90-5aed7fb30355"}
